---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Best Iconic Weapons & Where to Find Them - Cyberpunk 2077";
const description = "All Iconic weapons in Cyberpunk 2077 mapped with locations, stats, and which builds benefit most from each weapon.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="guide">
    <h1>🔫 Best Iconic Weapons & Where to Find Them</h1>

    <div class="intro">
      <p>Iconic weapons are unique, legendary weapons in Cyberpunk 2077. Each has special mods and effects that make them stand out. This guide covers the best Iconic weapons, where to find them, and which builds benefit most from each.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="overview">
      <h2>📊 Iconic Weapons Overview</h2>
      <p>Iconic weapons are tiered from Tier 1+ to Tier 5++. Higher tiers have better stats and more mod slots. You can upgrade Iconic weapons at a workbench using crafting components.</p>

      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>💡 Important:</strong> Iconic weapons cannot be crafted from scratch. You must find them in the world. However, you can upgrade them once you have them.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="top-weapons">
      <h2>🏆 Top 10 Iconic Weapons</h2>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>1. Nue (Smart Pistol)</h3>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Details</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Type</strong></td>
            <td>Smart Pistol (auto-targeting)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Damage</strong></td>
            <td>250-350 (varies by tier)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Special Effect</strong></td>
            <td>Bullets track enemies, +20% smart weapon damage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Best For</strong></td>
            <td>Netrunner builds, hybrid builds</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Location</strong></td>
            <td>Quest reward from "The Heist" mission</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p><strong>Why It's Great:</strong> Smart weapons are essential for Netrunner builds. You can focus on hacking while the gun handles aiming. Nue is one of the first Iconic weapons you get and remains viable throughout the game.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>2. Tactician (Tech Shotgun)</h3>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Details</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Type</strong></td>
            <td>Tech Shotgun (charges through walls)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Damage</strong></td>
            <td>800-1200 per shot (charged)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Special Effect</strong></td>
            <td>Charges shoot through walls, +40% tech weapon damage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Best For</strong></td>
            <td>Tech builds, burst damage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Location</strong></td>
            <td>Found in a locked safe during "The Heist" mission</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p><strong>Why It's Great:</strong> The Tactician can one-shot most enemies when fully charged. It shoots through walls, so you don't have to expose yourself. Essential for tech builds.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>3. Ashura (Assault Rifle)</h3>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Details</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Type</strong></td>
            <td>Assault Rifle</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Damage</strong></td>
            <td>180-250 per bullet</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Special Effect</strong></td>
            <td>High fire rate, +25% headshot damage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Best For</strong></td>
            <td>Reflexes builds, sustained damage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Location</strong></td>
            <td>Dropped by Royce during "The Pickup" mission</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p><strong>Why It's Great:</strong> Ashura has an incredibly high fire rate and excellent accuracy. It's perfect for mid-range combat and works well with Reflexes builds that focus on headshots.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>4. Guts (Power Shotgun)</h3>
        <table>
          <tr>
